Modifications by the streetCryptid project
------------------------------------------

In accordance with section 5 of the GNU AGPL, the changes made to the upstream
v0.3.1 source after it was vendored into this repository are dated and
described below.

2026-07 — Ported from iroh 0.98.2 to iroh 1.0.2, and made buildable as a
standalone / path dependency:

  * Cargo.toml
      - Bumped dependencies to the versions used by this app's iroh 1.0 stack:
        `iroh` 0.98.2 -> 1.0.2 (feature `unstable-custom-transports`),
        `iroh-base` 0.98 -> 1.0.2, `n0-watcher` 0.6 -> 1, `noq-udp` 0.10 -> 1,
        `noq-proto` 0.17 -> 1.
      - Removed workspace inheritance (`rust-version.workspace = true` ->
        `rust-version = "1.95"`) so the crate builds outside the upstream
        workspace; added `publish = false`.
      - Added this vendoring/modification header and updated the description.

  * src/transport/hook.rs — updated to the iroh 1.0 `EndpointHooks` API:
      - `after_handshake` now receives `&iroh::endpoint::Connection` instead of
        the removed `&ConnectionInfo`.
      - Dropped the `!path.is_closed()` filter: `Connection::paths()` in 1.0
        only returns currently-open paths and `Path::is_closed` no longer
        exists.
      - Switched the connection-close watcher from a cloned `Connection` to a
        `WeakConnectionHandle` (`conn.weak_handle().closed().await`), which the
        1.0 hook documentation requires so the hook does not keep the
        connection alive / disable close-on-drop.

  * src/transport/transport.rs — updated to the iroh 1.0
    `CustomEndpoint` / `CustomSender` traits:
      - `poll_recv` now fills a `&mut [RecvInfo]` slice, constructing entries
        with `RecvInfo::new(custom_addr, None)`, instead of writing
        `Addr::Custom(..)` into a `&mut [Addr]` slice.
      - `poll_send` gained the new `src: Option<&CustomAddr>` argument (unused
        by this single-homed transport).
      - Updated the corresponding imports and a unit test call site, plus a
        stale doc comment referencing the iroh version.

The upstream `examples/` directory was intentionally not vendored; it
demonstrates endpoint wiring that this checkpoint does not yet use.

No other source files were modified.
